Agreement_submitInput
├── when state is CLOSED
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when state is REJECTED
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when inputId is not recognized for current state
│   └── it should revert with InvalidInput
└── when inputId is valid for current state
    ├── it should emit InputAccepted
    ├── it should route to the correct internal handler
    ├── given inputId is ADJUDICATE and no CLOSE action is present
    │   └── it should emit InputAccepted with ACTIVE -> ACTIVE
    └── given inputId is ADJUDICATE and a CLOSE action is present
        └── it should emit InputAccepted with ACTIVE -> CLOSED

Agreement_handlePropose
├── it should store termsHash from ProposalData
├── it should store termsUri from ProposalData
├── it should set turn to the other party
├── it should set state to PROPOSED
├── it should emit ProposalSubmitted
└── it should emit AgreementStateChanged
NOTE: handlePropose is called by the constructor during deployment (via AgreementRegistry).
      No external auth check needed — caller is always the deployer.

Agreement_handleCounter
├── when caller is not the party whose turn it is
│   └── it should revert with NotYourTurn
└── when caller is the correct party
    ├── it should overwrite termsHash
    ├── it should overwrite termsUri
    ├── it should flip turn to the other party
    ├── given state was PROPOSED
    │   ├── it should set state to NEGOTIATING
    │   └── it should emit AgreementStateChanged
    ├── given state was NEGOTIATING
    │   └── it should remain in NEGOTIATING
    ├── it should emit ProposalSubmitted
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleAccept
├── when state is PROPOSED and caller is not the other party
│   └── it should revert with NotYourTurn
├── when state is NEGOTIATING and caller is not the party whose turn it is
│   └── it should revert with NotYourTurn
└── when caller is authorized
    ├── it should lock the terms (termsHash and termsUri immutable)
    ├── it should set state to ACCEPTED
    ├── it should emit AgreementStateChanged
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleReject
├── when state is PROPOSED and caller is not the other party
│   └── it should revert with NotYourTurn
└── when caller is authorized
    ├── it should set state to REJECTED
    ├── it should emit AgreementStateChanged
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleWithdraw
├── when state is not PROPOSED
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not parties[0] (proposer)
│   └── it should revert with NotYourTurn
└── when caller is parties[0] and state is PROPOSED
    ├── it should set state to REJECTED
    ├── it should emit AgreementStateChanged
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleSetUp
├── when state is not ACCEPTED
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not a party
│   └── it should revert with NotAParty
└── when caller is a party and state is ACCEPTED
    ├── given a zone has agentId != 0 and ownerOf(agentId) != party
    │   └── it should revert with AgentIdVerificationFailed
    ├── given zones length is 0 or > 2
    │   └── it should revert with InvalidZoneCount
    ├── given zones length is 1
    │   └── it should set up zone 0 only and transition to READY
    ├── given a zone party does not match the agreement party
    │   └── it should revert with NotAParty
    ├── given deadline is in the past or zero
    │   └── it should revert with DeadlineReached
    ├── given SET_UP called from READY
    │   └── it should revert with InvalidState
    └── given all validations pass
        ├── for each zone
        │   ├── it should create a zone hat via Hats Protocol
        │   ├── it should NOT mint the zone hat to the party
        │   ├── it should deploy a TrustZone clone via Clones.cloneDeterministic
        │   ├── it should initialize the TrustZone clone
        │   ├── given moduleKind is HatsModule and paramType is Eligibility or Penalty
        │   │   └── it should deploy via HatsModuleFactory with packed data and wire to zone hat
        │   ├── given moduleKind is HatsModule and paramType is not Eligibility or Penalty
        │   │   └── it should deploy via HatsModuleFactory with packed data but not wire to hat (standalone)
        │   ├── given moduleKind is ERC7579Hook
        │   │   ├── it should install as ERC-7579 hooks via HookMultiPlexer
        │   │   └── it should initialize sub-hooks with their data via executeFromExecutor
        │   ├── given moduleKind is External and data is non-empty
        │   │   └── it should call module.call(data) during setup
        │   ├── it should register all mechanisms in the mechanism registry (with moduleKind)
        │   ├── it should preserve mechanism data as stored mechanism context
        │   ├── it should store deployed clone address for HatsModule mechanisms in registry
        │   ├── it should replace sentinel hat IDs in initData with agreement hat ID
        │   ├── it should mint resource tokens to the TrustZone
        │   ├── it should emit ZoneDeployed
        │   ├── it should emit MechanismRegistered for each mechanism
        │   └── it should emit ResourceTokenAssigned for each token
        ├── given no hat-wired HatsModule mechanisms (Eligibility/Penalty)
        │   └── it should use the agreement as the default eligibility module
        ├── given multiple distinct ERC7579Hook mechanisms
        │   ├── it should install both hooks
        │   └── it should initialize both hooks with their data
        ├── it should store trustZones addresses
        ├── it should store zoneHatIds
        ├── it should store agentIds
        ├── it should set state to READY
        ├── it should emit AgreementSetUp
        └── it should emit AgreementStateChanged

Agreement_handleActivate
├── when state is not READY
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when state is ACCEPTED
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState (must SET_UP first)
├── when caller is not a party
│   └── it should revert with NotAParty
└── when caller is a party and state is READY
    ├── it should mint zone hats to parties via Hats Protocol
    ├── it should not redeploy zones or mechanisms
    ├── it should set state to ACTIVE
    ├── it should emit AgreementActivated
    └── it should emit AgreementStateChanged

Agreement_handleClaim
├── when state is not ACTIVE
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not a party
│   └── it should revert with NotAParty
├── when mechanismIndex is out of bounds
│   └── it should revert with InvalidMechanismIndex
├── when mechanismIndex refers to a CONSTRAINT mechanism
│   └── it should revert with InvalidMechanismIndex
└── when inputs are valid
    ├── it should increment claimCount
    ├── it should emit ClaimFiled
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleAdjudicate
├── when state is not ACTIVE
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not the adjudicator
│   └── it should revert with NotAdjudicator
├── when claimId is invalid
│   └── it should revert with InvalidClaimId
├── when claimId is already adjudicated
│   └── it should revert with ClaimAlreadyAdjudicated
├── when action execution reverts
│   └── it should leave the claim retryable
└── when inputs are valid
    ├── it should mark the claim as adjudicated
    ├── for each AdjudicationAction
    │   ├── given actionType is PENALIZE
    │   │   └── it should call the mechanism module with penalize params
    │   ├── given actionType is REWARD
    │   │   └── it should call the mechanism module with reward params
    │   ├── given actionType is FEEDBACK
    │   │   └── it should call reputationRegistry.giveFeedback
    │   ├── given actionType is DEACTIVATE
    │   │   ├── it should set _hatDeactivated[zoneHatId] to true
    │   │   └── it should call HATS.setHatStatus(zoneHatIds[action.targetIndex], false)
    │   ├── given actionType is DEACTIVATE and targetIndex is out of bounds
    │   │   └── it should revert with InvalidMechanismIndex
    │   └── given actionType is CLOSE
    │       └── it should trigger close with outcome ADJUDICATED
    ├── given multiple actions are present
    │   ├── it should execute them in order
    │   ├── it should support mixed PENALIZE + FEEDBACK + DEACTIVATE + CLOSE verdicts
    │   └── it should remain ACTIVE when no CLOSE action is present
    ├── given targetIndex is 1
    │   ├── it should write FEEDBACK for party B
    │   └── it should DEACTIVATE zone hat 1
    ├── given actionType is unknown
    │   └── it should preserve the documented fallback behavior
    ├── it should emit AdjudicationDelivered
    └── it should emit InputAccepted

Agreement_handleComplete
├── when state is not ACTIVE
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not a party
│   └── it should revert with NotAParty
├── when caller has already signaled completion
│   └── it should revert with AlreadySignaled
└── when caller has not yet signaled
    ├── it should store feedbackURI and feedbackHash for this party
    ├── it should set completionSignaled[partyIndex] to true
    ├── it should emit CompletionSignaled
    ├── given the other party has not yet signaled
    │   └── it should remain in ACTIVE
    └── given the other party has already signaled
        └── it should trigger close with outcome COMPLETED

Agreement_handleExit
├── when state is not ACTIVE
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when caller is not a party
│   └── it should revert with NotAParty
├── when caller has already signaled exit
│   └── it should revert with AlreadySignaled
└── when caller has not yet signaled
    ├── it should store feedbackURI and feedbackHash for this party
    ├── it should set exitSignaled[partyIndex] to true
    ├── it should emit ExitSignaled
    ├── given the other party has not yet signaled
    │   └── it should remain in ACTIVE
    └── given the other party has already signaled
        └── it should trigger close with outcome EXITED

Agreement_handleFinalize
├── when state is not ACTIVE
│   └── it should revert with InvalidState
├── when deadline has not passed
│   └── it should revert with DeadlineNotReached
└── when deadline has passed
    └── it should trigger close with outcome EXPIRED

Agreement_close
├── it should set state to CLOSED
├── it should store the outcome
├── it should deactivate zone hats via HATS.setHatStatus(hatId, false)
├── it should leave resource tokens held by each TrustZone
├── it should make TrustZone accounts inoperative after close
├── given a party has agentId != 0
│   ├── it should call reputationRegistry.giveFeedback
│   ├── it should use tag1 = "trust-zone-agreement"
│   ├── it should use tag2 = outcome string
│   ├── it should use endpoint = agreement address
│   ├── it should use counterparty's feedback URI and hash
│   └── it should emit ReputationFeedbackWritten for that party
├── given a party has agentId == 0
│   └── it should not call giveFeedback for that party
├── it should emit AgreementClosed
└── it should emit AgreementStateChanged

Agreement_getHatStatus
├── given hat has been explicitly deactivated via DEACTIVATE action
│   └── it should return false (even while ACTIVE + deadline OK)
├── given state is PROPOSED
│   └── it should return false
├── given state is ACCEPTED
│   └── it should return false
├── given state is READY
│   └── it should return true (hats exist but not yet worn)
├── given state is ACTIVE and deadline has passed
│   └── it should return false
├── given state is ACTIVE and deadline has not passed
│   └── it should return true
└── given state is CLOSED
    └── it should return false

Agreement_getters
├── docHash
│   └── it should return the stored terms hash
├── termsUri
│   └── it should return the stored terms URI
├── mechanisms
│   └── it should revert with InvalidMechanismIndex when index is out of bounds
├── getWearerStatus
│   └── it should return (true, true) in the default eligibility path
└── onUninstall
    └── it should be a no-op

Agreement_zoneBehavior
├── given a zone is ACTIVE and the caller wears its zone hat
│   ├── it should allow TrustZone.execute()
│   └── it should validate signatures via ERC-1271
├── given a configured CONSTRAINT hook forbids the action
│   └── it should block TrustZone.execute()
├── given a configured CONSTRAINT hook allows the action
│   └── it should allow TrustZone.execute()
├── given the zone hat has been explicitly deactivated
│   ├── it should reject TrustZone.execute()
│   └── it should fail ERC-1271 validation
└── given the agreement is CLOSED
    ├── it should reject TrustZone.execute()
    └── it should fail ERC-1271 validation

Agreement_invariants
├── terminal agreements reject all further inputs
├── state transitions follow the allowed state graph
├── outcome remains unset until close and immutable afterward
├── activation artifacts are immutable after activation
├── mechanism registry is frozen after activation
├── claimCount is monotonic
├── adjudicated claims are always a subset of filed claims
├── reverted adjudications do not consume claims
├── completion and exit signals are monotonic
├── closed agreements always have inactive zone hats
├── explicitly deactivated hats never become active again
├── each zone validator tracks its zone hat id
├── inactive zones cannot authorize execution or signatures
├── only authorized callers can execute through a zone
├── close preserves zone addresses but removes authority
├── activation-minted resource tokens are created by the agreement
├── registered mechanism zone indexes are always valid
├── zero agent ids never receive reputation writes
├── close feedback routing matches the outcome-specific rules
└── reverted composite actions leave no partial state
